From: Vincent Fortier <th0ma7@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 01 Jun 2026
Subject: [PATCH] parsers/hevc: don't drop the whole hvcC when an optional SEI fails

isom_write_hvcc() builds the HEVC configuration record (hvcC) by feeding each
parameter-set NAL to hvcc_add_nal_unit(). VPS, SPS, PPS and SEI shared the same
error path: any hvcc_add_nal_unit() failure did "goto end", skipping hvcc_write()
and producing an EMPTY hvcC.

hevc_qsv emits a very small (~6 byte) prefix SEI NAL that hvcc_add_nal_unit()
rejects, so the entire hvcC came out empty. In a transcoded stream this means the
MKV CodecPrivate / MP4 hvcC is 0 bytes: the HEVC track carries no decoder config,
players fall back to in-band parameter sets (or fail outright) -> "audio only".
hevc_vaapi emits a larger SEI that happens to parse, so it was unaffected.

Confirmed by tracing isom_write_hvcc():
  hevc_qsv:   add VPS ret=0, add SPS ret=0, add PPS ret=0, add SEI(len=6) ret=-1
              -> hvcc_write never reached -> CodecPrivate=0
  hevc_vaapi: add VPS/SPS/PPS/SEI(len=76) all ret=0 -> CodecPrivate=206

SEI is optional in the hvcC. Keep VPS/SPS/PPS mandatory (bail on failure), but add
SEI on a best-effort basis and ignore failures, so a malformed/tiny SEI no longer
discards the configuration record. h264 (avcC) is unaffected.

Suggested-by: Claude Opus 4.8 (Anthropic AI <https://anthropic.com>)
Signed-off-by: Vincent Fortier <th0ma7@gmail.com>

--- src/parsers/parser_hevc.c.orig	2026-05-19 20:37:17.000000000 +0000
+++ src/parsers/parser_hevc.c	2026-06-01 11:45:00.000000000 +0000
@@ -1164,12 +1164,20 @@
         case HEVC_NAL_VPS:
         case HEVC_NAL_SPS:
         case HEVC_NAL_PPS:
-        case HEVC_NAL_SEI_PREFIX:
-        case HEVC_NAL_SEI_SUFFIX:
+            /* VPS/SPS/PPS are mandatory: a parse failure means we cannot build a
+             * valid hvcC, so bail out. */
             ret = hvcc_add_nal_unit(buf, len, &hvcc);
             if (ret < 0)
                 goto end;
             break;
+        case HEVC_NAL_SEI_PREFIX:
+        case HEVC_NAL_SEI_SUFFIX:
+            /* SEI is optional in the hvcC. Some encoders (notably hevc_qsv) emit a
+             * tiny SEI NAL that hvcc_add_nal_unit() rejects; that must NOT discard
+             * the whole configuration record (which left an empty hvcC/CodecPrivate
+             * and an undecodable HEVC track). Add it best-effort and ignore errors. */
+            hvcc_add_nal_unit(buf, len, &hvcc);
+            break;
         default:
             break;
         }
